## Install

```bash
go get github.com/burl/inquire/v2@${TAG}
```

Requires Go 1.26+. Unix TTY on stdin and stdout.

## Quick start

```go
err := inquire.Query().
    Input(&name, "what is your name", nil).
    YesNo(&ok, "continue", nil).
    Run(ctx)
if errors.Is(err, inquire.ErrInterrupted) { /* Ctrl+C */ }
```

## Widgets

`Input` · `YesNo` · `Menu` · `Select` · `Note` · `AnyKey` — configure in the `more` callback on each `Query()` step.

```go
inquire.Query().
    Note("Bridge of Death", nil).
    Menu(&quest, "your quest", func(w *widget.Menu) {
        w.Item("grail", "find the grail")
    }).
    Input(&weight, "swallow weight", func(w *widget.Input) {
        w.When(widget.WhenEqual(&quest, "nuts"))
    })
```

